<!-- Start of Story -->
<div class="container marketing">
	<br>
	<center><h1>Our Story</h1></center>
	<br>
	<p>
	The Computational Biomedicine Laboratory (CBL) is currently directed by Professor Linwei Wang and is part of the Center for Advancing the 
	Study of Cyberinfrastructure (CASCI) at RIT. Funded by the NSF and the NIH, our research focus on computational systems biomedicine that 
	adapts systems approach and concept to biomedical problems of importance to public health. Standing on the intersection between computing 
	and biomedicine, we are seeking and developing methods, algorithms, and systems that will integrate the strength of physics-based modeling 
	with that of data-driven inference/learning methods toward the task of personalized physiological modeling. Integrating physics-based modeling 
	of complex systems into the understanding of data will place the data-driven inference in a domain-realistic context; developing advanced 
	probabilistic inference methods in combination with domain modeling will address the arising issues of uncertainty, robustness, and model-data 
	mismatch. In particular, the driving application area of the CBL lies in the electrophysiology and electromechanics of the heart, aiming for 
	transmural electrophysiological and electromechanical imaging for specific subjects using their physiologic mapping and medical imaging data.
	</p>
	<br> <center> <img src="images/cbl_logo.svg" style="width: 225px"> </center>
	<br>
	
